i just had my nd d c and my third miscarriage i'm devastated is something wrong with me i have two living kids ages and i got pregnant easily and carried both to term my husband and i wanted a third child and we got pregnant in feb of i lost that baby at weeks i got pregnant again in dec of lost that baby at weeks i just got pregnant in june got to weeks and lost my bobbie i'm very sad i was very attached to this one i almost made it to weeks should i give up is something wrong with me i'm only years old i feel like i'm broken and some freak who can only carry to weeeks now first i am so sorry for your loss sweetie i had a miscarriage in december at weeks so i know how devastating it is okay it's time to take charge of your fertility here after miscarriages doctors usually order tests on the rd one did your doctor do this two things keep jumping out at me here there's a chromosomal issue and low progesterone if it's a chromosomal issue a pathology report on your last d c will find it you can go from there and decide what you need to do if you didn't order a pathology report on this last one please please do so in the future should you miscarry or if you get pregnant you may want to strongly consider an amniocentisis given your history it could also be something as simple as low progesterone has your doctor ever tested you for this progesterone is responsible for a nice healthy uterine lining which is what the embyro needs to grow having low progesterone will allow you to get pregnant but not stay pregnant women with low progesterone commonly miscarry in the first trimester if this is the problem it's an easy fix your doctor would give you progesterone treatment until the th week when your placenta will take over the duty you may want to work with a high risk pregnancy specialist the next time around especially if your doctor didn't check your progesterone or order a pathology report this time around good luck Pregnancy Obstetrics In vitro fertilisation Childbirth Ab